extends BaseRepeater

    Base class for KivaKit projects, enabling run-time dependency management and initialization.

    Dependencies and Initialization

    Projects may declare dependencies on other projects that can be retrieved with dependencies(). These dependent projects can be visited with visitDependencies(Visitor), and initialization of a project with initialize() will cause transitive initialization of all dependencies in depth-first order. Subclasses of Project can provide initialization behavior by overriding onInitialize().

    Important Note: Project Initialization

    Projects that define a Project subclass, normally in the 'project' package of the project, should be initialized by calling initialize() before being used or undefined behavior can result. All KivaKit projects define a Project subclass. Project initialization occurs automatically for Applications.

    Properties

    Projects have several properties that can be queried:

    • build() - Build information
    • version() - The project version
    • kivakitVersion() - The version of KivaKit used by the project
    • properties() - System properties, environment variables and build properties for this project
